page.title: 07PRIVATE LAND USE
page.content:
In this area there are thirty-six garages, two greenhouses,one fuel store,one aviary, three barns, one car park, three out buildings and eleven garden sheds.
A garage is a building attached to a house, where you park your car. A greenhouse is a glass house that you grow plants in. An aviary is a bird house and a fuel store is a shed used to store coal or wood for burning. Barns are large sheds used to keep crops and tractors. A car ,park is a piece of land where you can park your car. Out buildings are small buildings that are used for general storage. Sheds are similar to out buildings, but are usually smaller.
